CSS Flexbox makes it easier to design flexible and responsive layouts. By using `display: flex`, you can align and distribute elements inside a container efficiently. Here’s a simple example:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

This centers the content both vertically and horizontally on the page.

Would you like me to show you an example using CSS Grid instead?

Sure! With CSS Grid, you can achieve the same centering effect using `place-items`. Here’s an example:

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

This produces the same centered layout, but Grid also provides more control over rows and columns if needed.
